Subscriptions

Sistema EGD API GraphQL V3

Bem-vindo(a) à documentação da API GraphQL V3 do Sistema EGD.

Contact

Suporte da API

contato@sistemaegd.com.br

API Endpoints
https://plataforma-edux-v3-dev.azurewebsites.net/graphql
Headers
# Token recuperado através da query 'token'
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_TOKEN_HERE>

Instruções

﻿

Sobre o que é essa API?

Os métodos presentes na API permitem ao consumidor integrar os dados de seu sistema de forma rápida e fácil, não importando qual tecnologia use 🦄🌌✨

Acessando a API

🛰 Os endpoints da API são:

Ambiente Url
Produção https://plataforma-edux-v3.azurewebsites.net/graphql
Desenvolvimento https://plataforma-edux-v3-dev.azurewebsites.net/graphql

📇 Para consumir as queries e mutations disponibilizadas nessa API, primeiro é necessário se autenticar:

query token(email: "email@escola.com.br", password: "s3Nh@", currentSchool: numero_da_escola) {
    token
}

Com o token em mãos, basta informar no cabeçãlho de cada chamada:

Authorization: Bearer <token_recuperado>

Queries

academicLevels

Response

Returns [AcademicLevel]

Arguments
Name Description
where - AcademicLevelFilterInput
order - [AcademicLevelSortInput!]

Example

Query
query AcademicLevels(
  $where: AcademicLevelFilterInput,
  $order: [AcademicLevelSortInput!]
) {
  academicLevels(
    where: $where,
    order: $order
  ) {
    id
    schoolId
    name
    averageExpressionId
    averageExpression {
      ...AverageExpressionFragment
    }
    school {
      ...SchoolFragment
    }
    compositeSchoolSubjectExpressions {
      ...CompositeSchoolSubjectExpressionFragment
    }
    compositeSchoolSubjects {
      ...CompositeSchoolSubjectFragment
    }
    courses {
      ...CourseFragment
    }
    studentSchoolTranscripts {
      ...StudentSchoolTranscriptFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "where": AcademicLevelFilterInput,
  "order": [AcademicLevelSortInput]
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "academicLevels": [
      {
        "id": 123,
        "schoolId": 987,
        "name": "xyz789",
        "averageExpressionId": 987,
        "averageExpression": AverageExpression,
        "school": School,
        "compositeSchoolSubjectExpressions": [
          CompositeSchoolSubjectExpression
        ],
        "compositeSchoolSubjects": [
          CompositeSchoolSubject
        ],
        "courses": [Course],
        "studentSchoolTranscripts": [
          StudentSchoolTranscript
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}

assessmentCategories

Response

Returns [AssessmentCategory]

Arguments
Name Description
where - AssessmentCategoryFilterInput
order - [AssessmentCategorySortInput!]

Example

Query
query AssessmentCategories(
  $where: AssessmentCategoryFilterInput,
  $order: [AssessmentCategorySortInput!]
) {
  assessmentCategories(
    where: $where,
    order: $order
  ) {
    id
    schoolId
    name
    abbreviation
    assessmentType
    assessmentShowType
    averageExpressionId
    assessmentPriority
    averageExpression {
      ...AverageExpressionFragment
    }
    school {
      ...SchoolFragment
    }
    courseAssessments {
      ...CourseAssessmentFragment
    }
    averageExpressions {
      ...AverageExpressionFragment
    }
    repleacements {
      ...AssessmentCategoryFragment
    }
    toReplaces {
      ...AssessmentCategoryFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "where": AssessmentCategoryFilterInput,
  "order": [AssessmentCategorySortInput]
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "assessmentCategories": [
      {
        "id": 987,
        "schoolId": 123,
        "name": "xyz789",
        "abbreviation": "abc123",
        "assessmentType": "NONE",
        "assessmentShowType": "NONE",
        "averageExpressionId": 123,
        "assessmentPriority": 123,
        "averageExpression": AverageExpression,
        "school": School,
        "courseAssessments": [CourseAssessment],
        "averageExpressions": [AverageExpression],
        "repleacements": [AssessmentCategory],
        "toReplaces": [AssessmentCategory]
      }
    ]
  }
}

Example

Query
query AverageExpression($averageExpressionId: Int!) {
  averageExpression(averageExpressionId: $averageExpressionId) {
    id
    title
    description
    expression
    humanFriendlyExpression
    averageExpressionType
    schoolId
    isActive
    school {
      ...SchoolFragment
    }
    academicLevels {
      ...AcademicLevelFragment
    }

      ...AssessmentCategoryFragment
    }

      ...CompositeSchoolSubjectExpressionFragment

    semiannualRecoveries {
      ...SemiannualRecoveryFragment
    }
    studentAverages {
      ...StudentAverageFragment
    }
    assessmentCategoriesNavigation {
      ...AssessmentCategoryFragment
    }
    schoolSubjects {
      ...SchoolSubjectFragment
    }
  }
}

{"averageExpressionId": 123}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "averageExpression": [

        "id": 123,
        "title": "abc123",
        "description": "abc123",

        "averageExpressionType": "NONE",
        "schoolId": 123,
        "isActive": true,
        "school": School,
        "academicLevels": [AcademicLevel],

) {
  courses(

    order: $order
  ) {
    id

    description

    recoveryExpression

    gradeMetrics {
      ...GradeMetricFragment
    }
    pendingDocumentations {
      ...PendingDocumentationFragment
    }
    schoolClasses {
      ...SchoolClassFragment
    }
    studentSchoolTranscripts {
      ...StudentSchoolTranscriptFragment
    }
    paymentPlans {
      ...PaymentPlanFragment
    }
    periods {
      ...PeriodFragment
    }
    schoolMasterSubjects {
      ...SchoolMasterSubjectFragment
    }

Types

ID

Description

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

Example
4

Fields
Input Field Description
useDefaultSystem - Boolean!

Informa se o sistema deverá gerar os valores padrões para ano letivo e níveis acadêmicos (período letivo ainda deverá ser informado)
periodSchool - InitPeriodSchoolInput!

Configura o ano letivo da escola
periodType - PeriodType!

Configura qual o período letivo da escola
academicLevels - [InitAcademicLevelInput]!

Configura os níveis acadêmicos da escola
studentParents - [InitFamilyInput]!

Informa os responsáveis e seus filhos matriculados na escola
Example
{
  "useDefaultSystem": false,
  "periodSchool": InitPeriodSchoolInput,
  "periodType": "BIMESTRE",
  "academicLevels": [InitAcademicLevelInput],
  "studentParents": [InitFamilyInput]
}
Types

InitSex

Description

Values
Enum Value Description

NAO_INFORMADO

 NaoInformado

MASCULINO

 Masculino

FEMININO

 Feminino
Example
"NAO_INFORMADO"

Int

Description

The Int scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

Description

The Long scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole 64-bit numeric values. Long can represent values between -(2^63) and 2^63 - 1.

Subscriptions

onRolesChanged

Response

Returns a UserRolesChanged

Arguments
Name Description
userId - String

Example

Query
subscription OnRolesChanged($userId: String) {
  onRolesChanged(userId: $userId) {
    userId
    roles
  }
}
Variables
{"userId": "xyz789"}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "onRolesChanged": {
      "userId": "xyz789",
      "roles": ["xyz789"]
    }
  }
}
